  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide a comprehensive, integrated and community package for mental health and psychosocial support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1)	Continuous provision of a comprehensive package of mental health services. Improve the capacity of MHPSS actors, healthcare- and humanitarian workers to increase their response to GBV. Promote reconciliation and social cohesion in Telafar.
2)	Continuous provision of services for people with disabilities: basic physical rehabilitation, screening and referral services in Sinjar and Telafar.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDPs, Returnees &amp; Host communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With this increasing number of returnees, the need for more sustainable MHPSS, GBV and PR services is getting higher. DoH is not ready for the hand-over process and is not able yet to run the departments of MHPSS and PR all by itself. In order to see a positive impact on personal and community level, with no other actors in the areas, a long-term project (one year or more) in Telafar and Sinjar is required to cover 340,356 returnee in Telafar and 68,130 returnee in Sinjar districts of Ninawa governorate.

The project is designed to respond to the needs of the vulnerable targeted returnees dis-aggregated by age group and gender, especially women and adolescent girls (+ 12 years old) who are more prone for GBV and Psychosocial suffering.</narrative>
  </description>
